Serviceable Mexican food when you're in a pinch. The food comes out quickly and they have a whole board of specials like 3 tacos and a soda for $10.95, which is a pretty good deal around these parts. Inspired to get something healthy following my workout at Beast Fitness around the corner, I opted for a Baja salad.  It comes with a huge seared piece of tilapia that sits atop a bowl of mainly iceberg lettuce and arugula. While the protein portion was pretty sizeable, it was fishier than I would've liked. The salad comes with a dressing on the side to add some flavor to the mixed greens. My partner ordered a grilled steak burrito and also thought it was serviceable but not terribly exciting. Folks seem to rave about their tacos, so I might order those if I find myself returning.

Came to Fatty Daddy during the week when both my boyfriend and I had off so we could try it.  I ordered the lunch special, 2 tacos and a soda (forgot the price). I got the fish tacos and the pastor. I must say I really enjoyed the fish taco I thought it was delicious. The sauce it comes with was very good, not spicy. The pastor tacos were delicious also. I really like that the tortillas arnt super soft, they have a slight crunch to them. My boyfriend got the chicken quesadilla. It was packed with meat ! And the cheese they use is perfect (I'm not a cheese lover/expert so I don't know what kind it was)  We ate inside and although it is small it has more seating than I thought. From the outside I thought it was just 4 or 5 seats along the window but there are a couple more. I would definitely come here again. Worth the money.

I love this place and all of there food. i have been going for years and don't have a complaint. Everything is reasonable and well prepared. The staff is mostly nice with the occasional snark and smear, but its a small place with a big clientele so i get it. Food takes a minute because of all the seamless orders, but when it comes.......boy is it amazing. The only issue I can honestly say about them is that there little restaurant SUCKS atmospherically. NYC is cold during the winter and let me tell you eating in here will be like eating outside. There is no heat and the only thing keeping the cold out is a useless ripped, dirty, door cover. I am telling you that while it may be cold this is some awesome food and I cannot really complain at all.
